  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Legal Elements\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Creating mechanisms for investigating suspicious transactions\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must:\n- Screen customers\n- Monitor transactions\n- Report suspicious activities\n- Maintain detailed transaction records\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n6. Technological Considerations\n- Advanced monitoring systems\n- Digital transaction tracking\n- Blockchain and cryptocurrency regulations\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
